-- Ecuador’s Leon to Head Agriculture Ministry After Vera Resigns
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-02-14T16:36:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/ecuador-s-leon-to-head-agriculture-ministry-after-vera-resigns.html
Ecuador’s government said Production
Minister Santiago Leon will take charge of the nation’s
 Agriculture Ministry  until a permanent replacement for Minister
Wilfrido Staynley Vera is named.  Leon was appointed today by presidential decree, the
Production Ministry said in a statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Nathan Gill  in  Quito  at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at   jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 